## 🔑 Environment Variables Summary

### Render (Backend)

| Variable | Value | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `postgresql://user:pass@host/db` | PostgreSQL connection string |
| `SECRET_KEY` | Random string | Flask session security |
| `JWT_SECRET_KEY` | Random string | JWT token signing |
| `RENDER` | *(auto-set by Render)* | Triggers ProductionConfig |

### Vercel (Frontend)

| Variable | Value | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_API_URL` | `https://nextgen-campus-1.onrender.com/api` | Points frontend to backend |

> [!WARNING]
> The `VITE_API_URL` must include `/api` at the end! The backend routes are all under `/api/*`.

---

## 🛠️ Render Dashboard Settings (Manual Setup)

If you created the service manually instead of using Blueprint:

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| **Root Directory** | *(leave blank)* |
| **Build Command** | `cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt` |
| **Start Command** | `gunicorn --chdir backend run:app` |

**Why `gunicorn --chdir backend run:app`?**
- `--chdir backend` tells Gunicorn to change into the `backend/` directory before importing
- `run:app` means import the [app](file:///Users/vishnu/next%20campus/backend/app/__init__.py#7-47) variable from [run.py](file:///Users/vishnu/next%20campus/backend/run.py)
- Without `--chdir`, Gunicorn looks for [run.py](file:///Users/vishnu/next%20campus/backend/run.py) in the repo root and fails with `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'run'`

